Apprenticeship – IT Specialist,ELCA,Schweiz,2026-01-30T21:49:12Z,https://www.adzuna.ch/details/5606821924?utm_medium=api&utm_source=026d8627,https://www.adzuna.ch/details/5606821924,,,"Description We are looking for a motivated IT Specialist CFC apprentice to join our Information Technology department. This apprenticeship offers a unique opportunity to gain hands-on experience across multiple IT domains, including operations, infrastructure, customer service, and cybersecurity, while working alongside experienced professionals. What you will learn: 1st Year: Prepare and set up c",it operations,4,0,79,False,False,strict,adzuna,"Description We are looking for a motivated IT Specialist CFC apprentice to join our Information Technology department. This apprenticeship offers a unique opportunity to gain hands-on experience across multiple IT domains, including operations, infrastructure, customer service, and cybersecurity, while working alongside experienced professionals. What you will learn: 1st Year: Prepare and set up computers and devices for employees Provide IT support and services to users 2nd Year: Help manage IT infrastructure Learn how systems and networks work in a professional environment 3rd Year: One-year internship with ECS, focused on customer service and user support 4th Year: One-year internship in the Security Department Learn the basics of IT security and best practices Your profile You are comfortable with math You have a good level of English (some meetings are held in English) You enjoy working with people and communicating You are curious, motivated, and passionate about IT You want to learn, grow, and build a future in technology Please send us your complete application , including: Cover letter CV School transcripts from the last three years",1159,400,"Description We are looking for a motivated IT Specialist CFC apprentice to join our Information Technology department. This apprenticeship offers a unique opportunity to gain hands-on experience across multiple IT domains, including operations, infrastructure, customer service, and cybersecurity, while working alongside experienced professionals. What you will learn: 1st Year: Prepare and set up computers and devices for employees Provide IT support and services to users 2nd Year: Help manage IT infrastructure Learn how systems and networks work in a professional environment 3rd Year: One-year internship with ECS, focused on customer service and user support 4th Year: One-year internship in the Security Department Learn the basics of IT security and best practices Your profile You are comfortable with math You have a good level of English (some meetings are held in English) You enjoy working with people and communicating You are curious, motivated, and passionate about IT You want to learn, grow, and build a future in technology Please send us your complete application , including: Cover letter CV School transcripts from the last three years",1159,True,,True,True,True,False,False,False,,,,False,False,False,False,
Network Operations Engineer (Remote from Switzerland),Jobgether,Schweiz,2026-02-12T22:19:27Z,https://www.adzuna.ch/details/5626697182?utm_medium=api&utm_source=026d8627,https://www.adzuna.ch/details/5626697182,,,"This position is posted by Jobgether on behalf of a partner company. We are currently looking for a Network Operations Engineer in Switzerland. This role is central to ensuring that a modern telecommunications network remains reliable, scalable, and efficient. You will be responsible for monitoring, maintaining, and improving network systems while collaborating with engineering and operations team",operations engineer,0,0,76,True,False,strict,adzuna,"This position is posted by Jobgether on behalf of a partner company. We are currently looking for a Network Operations Engineer in Switzerland. This role is central to ensuring that a modern telecommunications network remains reliable, scalable, and efficient. You will be responsible for monitoring, maintaining, and improving network systems while collaborating with engineering and operations teams across various environments. The Network Operations Engineer will actively contribute to problem-solving, quality assurance, and continuous improvement initiatives that directly impact service quality and customer experience. This position requires technical proficiency, independent judgment, and a collaborative mindset to resolve network challenges effectively. You will engage in both routine operations and strategic network enhancements, ensuring high performance across all systems. The environment is dynamic, supportive, and focused on delivering innovative and high-quality network services.Accountabilities: Monitor, operate, and support day-to-day network systems with intermediate to advanced proficiency. Assist with testing, quality assurance, and validation of network infrastructure and services. Investigate network issues, determine root causes, and implement corrective or preventive actions. Recommend improvements to network systems, tools, and operational processes. Collaborate across engineering, operations, and product teams to support network reliability and scalability. Contribute technical expertise and insights to enhance overall system performance and customer experience. Requirements: 2–4 years of experience in network operations, network engineering, or related technical roles.Bachelor’s degree in a relevant field or equivalent practical experience.Strong understanding of network design, development, and maintenance of complex systems.Ability to resolve moderately complex technical problems within established guidelines.Excellent collaboration skills and ability to build effective working relationships across teams.Comfortable working independently with general supervision and clear objectives.Strong analytical and troubleshooting capabilities, with attention to detail. Benefits: Competitive base salary depending on location, experience, and qualifications.Flexible, remote-friendly work environment.Opportunities to contribute to a high-performing, customer-focused network.Paid time off, wellness allowances, and professional development support.Collaborative and innovative workplace culture focused on impact and quality.Access to a comprehensive total rewards program including benefits and potential incentives. Why Apply Through Jobgether? We use an AI-powered matching process to ensure your application is reviewed quickly, objectively, and fairly against the role's core requirements. Our system identifies the top-fitting candidates, and this shortlist is then shared directly with the hiring company. The final decision and next steps (interviews, assessments) are managed by their internal team.We appreciate your interest and wish you the best! Why Apply Through Jobgether? Data Privacy Notice: By submitting your application, you acknowledge that Jobgether will process your personal data to evaluate your candidacy and share relevant information with the hiring employer. This processing is based on legitimate interest and pre-contractual measures under applicable data protection laws (including GDPR). You may exercise your rights (access, rectification, erasure, objection) at any time. #LI-CL1We may use artificial intelligence (AI) tools to support parts of the hiring process, such as reviewing applications, analyzing resumes, or assessing responses. These tools assist our recruitment team but do not replace human judgment. Final hiring decisions are ultimately made by humans. If you would like more information about how your data is processed, please contact us.",3943,400,"This position is posted by Jobgether on behalf of a partner company. We are currently looking for a Network Operations Engineer in Switzerland. This role is central to ensuring that a modern telecommunications network remains reliable, scalable, and efficient. You will be responsible for monitoring, maintaining, and improving network systems while collaborating with engineering and operations teams across various environments. The Network Operations Engineer will actively contribute to problem-solving, quality assurance, and continuous improvement initiatives that directly impact service quality and customer experience. This position requires technical proficiency, independent judgment, and a collaborative mindset to resolve network challenges effectively. You will engage in both routine operations and strategic network enhancements, ensuring high performance across all systems. The environment is dynamic, supportive, and focused on delivering innovative and high-quality network services.Accountabilities: Monitor, operate, and support day-to-day network systems with intermediate to advanced proficiency. Assist with testing, quality assurance, and validation of network infrastructure and services. Investigate network issues, determine root causes, and implement corrective or preventive actions. Recommend improvements to network systems, tools, and operational processes. Collaborate across engineering, operations, and product teams to support network reliability and scalability. Contribute technical expertise and insights to enhance overall system performance and customer experience. Requirements: 2–4 years of experience in network operations, network engineering, or related technical roles.Bachelor’s degree in a relevant field or equivalent practical experience.Strong understanding of network design, development, and maintenance of complex systems.Ability to resolve moderately complex technical problems within established guidelines.Excellent collaboration skills and ability to build effective working relationships across teams.Comfortable working independently with general supervision and clear objectives.Strong analytical and troubleshooting capabilities, with attention to detail. Benefits: Competitive base salary depending on location, experience, and qualifications.Flexible, remote-friendly work environment.Opportunities to contribute to a high-performing, customer-focused network.Paid time off, wellness allowances, and professional development support.Collaborative and innovative workplace culture focused on impact and quality.Access to a comprehensive total rewards program including benefits and potential incentives. Why Apply Through Jobgether? We use an AI-powered matching process to ensure your application is reviewed quickly, objectively, and fairly against the role's core requirements. Our system identifies the top-fitting candidates, and this shortlist is then shared directly with the hiring company. The final decision and next steps (interviews, assessments) are managed by their internal team.We appreciate your interest and wish you the best! Why Apply Through Jobgether? Data Privacy Notice: By submitting your application, you acknowledge that Jobgether will process your personal data to evaluate your candidacy and share relevant information with the hiring employer. This processing is based on legitimate interest and pre-contractual measures under applicable data protection laws (including GDPR). You may exercise your rights (access, rectification, erasure, objection) at any time. #LI-CL1We may use artificial intelligence (AI) tools to support parts of the hiring process, such as reviewing applications, analyzing resumes, or assessing responses. These tools assist our recruitment team but do not replace human judgment. Final hiring decisions are ultimately made by humans. If you would like more information about how your data is processed, please contact us.",3943,True,,True,False,True,False,False,True,role_forbidden:artificial intelligence,"artificial intelligence, expert","artificial intelligence, expert",False,False,False,False,role_forbidden:artificial intelligence
Linux System Administrator,SThree Germany,Zürich,2026-02-06T22:36:27Z,https://www.adzuna.ch/details/5618092664?utm_medium=api&utm_source=026d8627,https://www.adzuna.ch/details/5618092664,2080.0,4160.0,"Linux System Administrator Start: ASAP - 3-4 months Extension Option: Yes, possible Workload: 80-100% Location: Zurich, Switzerland (hybrid) Your Mission Own the Linux workstation lifecycle from provisioning to decommissioning Own and evolve centralized configuration/update management for Linux end-user devices in R&D. Balance standardization with developer flexibility Define and enforce security ",system administrator,0,0,76,True,False,strict,adzuna,"Linux System Administrator Start: ASAP - 3-4 months Extension Option: Yes, possible Workload: 80-100% Location: Zurich, Switzerland (hybrid) Your Mission Own the Linux workstation lifecycle from provisioning to decommissioning Own and evolve centralized configuration/update management for Linux end-user devices in R&D. Balance standardization with developer flexibility Define and enforce security baselines and hardening standards Provide hands-on support for Linux device setup and tooling Collaborate closely with the Group IT team on policies, tooling, integrations & issue resolution Your Skillset Degree in Software Engineering or a related technical field. Able to work very independently & proactive problem-solver Proven experience administering Linux endpoints in a professional environment. Strong expertise in endpoint management frameworks for monitoring and fleet configuration under Linux. Deep understanding of the Linux ecosystem (Ubuntu / Nix) Solid knowledge of IT topics such as networking, VPN, security, device encryption, authentication and certificate management.Excellent communication skills and strong self-drive and self-organization skills SThree_Germany is acting as an Employment Business in relation to this vacancy.",1250,400,"Linux System Administrator Start: ASAP - 3-4 months Extension Option: Yes, possible Workload: 80-100% Location: Zurich, Switzerland (hybrid) Your Mission Own the Linux workstation lifecycle from provisioning to decommissioning Own and evolve centralized configuration/update management for Linux end-user devices in R&D. Balance standardization with developer flexibility Define and enforce security baselines and hardening standards Provide hands-on support for Linux device setup and tooling Collaborate closely with the Group IT team on policies, tooling, integrations & issue resolution Your Skillset Degree in Software Engineering or a related technical field. Able to work very independently & proactive problem-solver Proven experience administering Linux endpoints in a professional environment. Strong expertise in endpoint management frameworks for monitoring and fleet configuration under Linux. Deep understanding of the Linux ecosystem (Ubuntu / Nix) Solid knowledge of IT topics such as networking, VPN, security, device encryption, authentication and certificate management.Excellent communication skills and strong self-drive and self-organization skills SThree_Germany is acting as an Employment Business in relation to this vacancy.",1250,True,,True,False,True,False,False,True,role_forbidden:software engineer,expert,expert,False,False,False,False,role_forbidden:software engineer
Développeur Logiciels Embarqués,Job-Room,"Plan-les-Ouates, Genf",2026-02-06T05:50:41Z,https://www.adzuna.ch/details/5616877623?utm_medium=api&utm_source=026d8627,https://www.adzuna.ch/details/5616877623,,,"* 04 février 2026 * 100% * Temporaire * anglais (Courant), français (Courant) * Ch. du pont du centenaire 109, 1228 Plan-les-Ouates * Se connecter pour voir l-estimation de jobup.ch Rejoins une équipe dynamique et innovante, au cœur de la transformation du stationnement intelligent et développe de nouveaux produits embarqués et communicants. Acteur majeur des solutions de stationnement en Europe l",ingenieur systeme,0,11,76,False,False,strict,adzuna,"* 04 février 2026 * 100% * Temporaire * anglais (Courant), français (Courant) * Ch. du pont du centenaire 109, 1228 Plan-les-Ouates * Se connecter pour voir l-estimation de jobup.ch **Rejoins une équipe dynamique et innovante, au cœur de la transformation du stationnement intelligent et développe de nouveaux produits embarqués et communicants.** Acteur majeur des solutions de stationnement en Europe la force d-IEM Group réside dans sa capacité à innover et à entretenir une synergie entre les différents métiers impliqués. Fondée et dirigée par des ingénieurs, l-entreprise développe la majorité de ses produits en interne. IEM S.A. est à la recherche, pour un renfort temporaire de son équipe, un.e **Développeur.euse Logiciels Embarqués** ** Contrat à durée maximale de 12 mois** Entrée en fonction au plus vite Lieu de travail: Plan les Ouates **Ta mission** Avec une formation d-ingénieur en système embarqué, de développeur applicatif ou une solide expérience jugée équivalente, tu intègres l-équipe « embedded », composée aujourd-hui de 7 personnes. Tu participes à la création du logiciel de ces produits en collaboration avec les ingénieurs hardware et logiciel. Tu collabores aussi avec l-équipe « digitale » en charge de la partie serveur et centralisation, avec laquelle les produits communiquent. **Tes responsabilités principales** * Développement applicatif métier (Go) * Développement de composants logiciels (applications, librairies, services) sous Linux embarqué (Go, C) * Maintenance et amélioration des produits existants * Développement de fonctionnalités métier spécifiques au stationnement * Support interne (filiales, ventes) et externe (clients finaux) * Participation à la conception de l-architecture des produits et proposition de solutions techniques * Rédaction de spécifications techniques et documentation * Mise en place de tests automatisés **Compétences techniques** * Expérience d-au moins 3 ans dans le développement de logiciels embarqués * Maîtrise d-un langage haut niveau, idéalement Go * Aisance avec git et GitHub * Compétences en scripts, outils de debug et de tests * Capacité à prendre la responsabilité de petits projets ou lots de développement, de la planification à la livraison, en veillant à la qualité et au respect des délais * Expérience en développement de systèmes Linux embarqués (buildroot) (un plus) * Expérience en développement noyau Linux et compréhension de la chaîne de boot (un plus) **Compétences relationnelles** * Fort esprit d-équipe, avec la capacité à travailler en synergie autour d-objectifs communs * Autonomie et sens des responsabilités, notamment dans la gestion de petits projets ou lots de développement * Appétence pour les bonnes pratiques de développement et volonté de produire un code maintenable * Ouverture d-esprit, capacité à questionner les pratiques et à recevoir du feedback constructif * Excellente communication, capacité à évoluer dans une organisation à taille humaine avec des profils variés * Langues utilisées : français et anglais (maîtrise de l-italien un plus) * Esprit analytique et capacité à résoudre des problèmes complexes",3133,400,"* 04 février 2026 * 100% * Temporaire * anglais (Courant), français (Courant) * Ch. du pont du centenaire 109, 1228 Plan-les-Ouates * Se connecter pour voir l-estimation de jobup.ch **Rejoins une équipe dynamique et innovante, au cœur de la transformation du stationnement intelligent et développe de nouveaux produits embarqués et communicants.** Acteur majeur des solutions de stationnement en Europe la force d-IEM Group réside dans sa capacité à innover et à entretenir une synergie entre les différents métiers impliqués. Fondée et dirigée par des ingénieurs, l-entreprise développe la majorité de ses produits en interne. IEM S.A. est à la recherche, pour un renfort temporaire de son équipe, un.e **Développeur.euse Logiciels Embarqués** ** Contrat à durée maximale de 12 mois** Entrée en fonction au plus vite Lieu de travail: Plan les Ouates **Ta mission** Avec une formation d-ingénieur en système embarqué, de développeur applicatif ou une solide expérience jugée équivalente, tu intègres l-équipe « embedded », composée aujourd-hui de 7 personnes. Tu participes à la création du logiciel de ces produits en collaboration avec les ingénieurs hardware et logiciel. Tu collabores aussi avec l-équipe « digitale » en charge de la partie serveur et centralisation, avec laquelle les produits communiquent. **Tes responsabilités principales** * Développement applicatif métier (Go) * Développement de composants logiciels (applications, librairies, services) sous Linux embarqué (Go, C) * Maintenance et amélioration des produits existants * Développement de fonctionnalités métier spécifiques au stationnement * Support interne (filiales, ventes) et externe (clients finaux) * Participation à la conception de l-architecture des produits et proposition de solutions techniques * Rédaction de spécifications techniques et documentation * Mise en place de tests automatisés **Compétences techniques** * Expérience d-au moins 3 ans dans le développement de logiciels embarqués * Maîtrise d-un langage haut niveau, idéalement Go * Aisance avec git et GitHub * Compétences en scripts, outils de debug et de tests * Capacité à prendre la responsabilité de petits projets ou lots de développement, de la planification à la livraison, en veillant à la qualité et au respect des délais * Expérience en développement de systèmes Linux embarqués (buildroot) (un plus) * Expérience en développement noyau Linux et compréhension de la chaîne de boot (un plus) **Compétences relationnelles** * Fort esprit d-équipe, avec la capacité à travailler en synergie autour d-objectifs communs * Autonomie et sens des responsabilités, notamment dans la gestion de petits projets ou lots de développement * Appétence pour les bonnes pratiques de développement et volonté de produire un code maintenable * Ouverture d-esprit, capacité à questionner les pratiques et à recevoir du feedback constructif * Excellente communication, capacité à évoluer dans une organisation à taille humaine avec des profils variés * Langues utilisées : français et anglais (maîtrise de l-italien un plus) * Esprit analytique et capacité à résoudre des problèmes complexes",3133,True,,True,False,True,False,False,True,exclude_keyword:principal,"architect, au moins 3 ans, embedded, hardware, principal, solide experience","architect, au moins 3 ans, embedded, hardware, principal, solide experience",False,False,False,False,exclude_keyword:principal
