com is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited CVs. Contact person Melek VatanacanTalent Acquisition Manager+41 (79) 9284025 Your homebase Swisscom (Schweiz) AGPfingstweidstrasse 51, 8005 Zürich",3555,400,"Your future starts here Disclaimer: This text was created from the most frequently advertised jobs last year. Make changes to it so that the text/bullet points match your job. Note that you have included 4 bullet points for the highlights and 8 bullet points for the skills (hard & soft skills) and remove the bullet points that do not apply. Remove this text so that it does not appear in the published advert. You work in an agile team and are responsible for the development, automation and integration of customised solutions. You will use modern methods and tools and contribute to the continuous improvement of our systems. Together with your team colleagues, you will ensure that the solutions are always up to date and function optimally. Through your commitment, you will make an important contribution to the digital transformation and further development of our IT infrastructure. You are responsible for the development, implementation and operation of applications in an agile DevOps team Administration and optimisation of Kubernetes clusters and automated CI/CD strategies Development and operation of cloud native applications and integration of modern technologies Carrying out root cause analyses and finding solutions for application problems Supporting the further development and automation of technical workflows and processes Implementation and administration of Windows and Linux servers and network connections Collaboration in an agile team Utilising the latest technologies to promote digital transformation Your skills Degree (Uni/ETH/UAS) in computer science or comparable professional experience Several years of experience in the development, provision and administration of cloud native applications (Kubernetes, AWS, OpenShift) Knowledge of Windows and Linux server operating systems and Active Directory Knowledge of scripting and automation (e.g. PowerShell, Bash, Ansible, Python) Experience with web technologies and APIs (JavaScript, HTML, REST APIs) Good knowledge of network technologies and security (TCP/IP, DNS) Experience with modern DevOps practices and CI/CD tools Experience in agile ways of working and methods (SAFe, Scrum) Willingness to work on call and handle incidents and changes High resilience and the ability to penetrate complex problems Strong customer and service orientation Very good German and English Disclaimer: Please rewrite this text if it does not match your position. Also remove this help-text so that it does not appear in the job description. With us, you have the opportunity to work in one of our offices in Switzerland or in your home office. You will come into contact with agile working methods and the latest technologies. We offer flexible working hours to meet your personal needs. As a Swisscom employee, you can look forward to a variety of attractive benefits that will enrich your work experience. These include a pleasant working environment, financial benefits and exciting opportunities for professional development. Discover your Benefits. Is it a match? Apply now. Discover your possibilities Any questions? Here you'll find answers to the most important and frequently asked questions. To all recruitment agencies: Swisscom does not accept agency CVs. Please do not forward CVs to our job's alias, Swisscom employees or any other organisation location. Swisscom is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited CVs. Contact person Melek VatanacanTalent Acquisition Manager+41 (79) 9284025 Your homebase Swisscom (Schweiz) AGPfingstweidstrasse 51, 8005 Zürich",3555,True,,True,False,True,False,False,True,exclude_keyword:manager,"director, manager","director, manager",False,True,False,False,exclude_keyword:manager
DevOps Engineer (Hybrid Backend),Auterion,Schweiz,2026-01-28T21:49:31Z,https://www.adzuna.ch/details/5603986063?utm_medium=api&utm_source=026d8627,https://www.adzuna.ch/details/5603986063,,,"We are looking for a hands-on DevOps Engineer who loves infrastructure but isn't afraid to dive into application code. In this role, you will own our cloud infrastructure, automate our pipelines, and ensure our systems are secure and cost-efficient. Unlike traditional DevOps roles, you will also be an active contributor to our backend codebase. You will work closely with the development team to bu",devops,0,0,64,True,False,strict,adzuna,"We are looking for a hands-on DevOps Engineer who loves infrastructure but isn't afraid to dive into application code. In this role, you will own our cloud infrastructure, automate our pipelines, and ensure our systems are secure and cost-efficient. Unlike traditional DevOps roles, you will also be an active contributor to our backend codebase. You will work closely with the development team to build new features, maintain microservices, and ensure our Node.js and Python services are scalable and performant. Responsibilities and Duties Maintain, migrate, and scale our AWS infrastructure using Terraform and best practices for EC2, ECS, and data storage. Maintain and optimize our build/deploy pipelines using GoCD and GitHub Actions to ensure seamless delivery of our polyglot services (Node, Python, Rust, C++). Manage Docker images and orchestration on ECS to ensure consistent environments from dev to production. Implement and monitor metrics, logs, and alerts using Datadog. Proactively analyze traffic patterns to prevent issues before they impact users. Take ownership of infrastructure compliance standards, specifically maintaining requirements for SOC2. Analyze usage patterns and implement strategies to reduce AWS infrastructure costs without sacrificing performance. Assist the development team by writing and maintaining backend features in Node.js (TypeScript) and Python. Clean up, upgrade, and refactor existing services to reduce technical debt. Maintain and improve integrations with 3rd party services. Qualifications and Skills 3+ years of experience in a DevOps or SRE role. Strong proficiency with AWS core services (EC2, ECS, ECR, RDS, IAM). Production experience with Infrastructure as Code (Terraform). Solid experience with Docker and container orchestration. Coding Proficiency: You must be comfortable reading and writing production code in Node.js/TypeScript or Python. Experience building or maintaining CI/CD pipelines is a must (GoCD and GitHub Actions preferred). Experience with monitoring tools (Datadog, New Relic, or Prometheus). Experience navigating a polyglot environment (C++ or Rust build processes) is a plus. Knowledge of Database administration (Postgres) using ORMs (Prisma) is a plus. Experience handling infrastructure SOC2 compliance requirements is a plus. Benefits Flexible working hours Stock Options Generous holiday allowance Company pension plan Car parking Enhanced maternity & paternity leave Mental health and wellbeing support Learning and development opportunities About Auterion We are building the leading software platform for AI-powered autonomous systems for enterprise and government customers. Our team is supporting the most important missions and solving the most challenging problems. At Auterion, we bring together the sharpest minds who love to solve the hardest problems. Join a vibrant team built on innovation, openness, and excellence, where you’ll be empowered to develop ideas, collaborate across all levels, and make an impact that matters.",3027,400,"We are looking for a hands-on DevOps Engineer who loves infrastructure but isn't afraid to dive into application code. In this role, you will own our cloud infrastructure, automate our pipelines, and ensure our systems are secure and cost-efficient. Unlike traditional DevOps roles, you will also be an active contributor to our backend codebase. You will work closely with the development team to build new features, maintain microservices, and ensure our Node.js and Python services are scalable and performant. Responsibilities and Duties Maintain, migrate, and scale our AWS infrastructure using Terraform and best practices for EC2, ECS, and data storage. Maintain and optimize our build/deploy pipelines using GoCD and GitHub Actions to ensure seamless delivery of our polyglot services (Node, Python, Rust, C++). Manage Docker images and orchestration on ECS to ensure consistent environments from dev to production. Implement and monitor metrics, logs, and alerts using Datadog. Proactively analyze traffic patterns to prevent issues before they impact users. Take ownership of infrastructure compliance standards, specifically maintaining requirements for SOC2. Analyze usage patterns and implement strategies to reduce AWS infrastructure costs without sacrificing performance. Assist the development team by writing and maintaining backend features in Node.js (TypeScript) and Python. Clean up, upgrade, and refactor existing services to reduce technical debt. Maintain and improve integrations with 3rd party services. Qualifications and Skills 3+ years of experience in a DevOps or SRE role. Strong proficiency with AWS core services (EC2, ECS, ECR, RDS, IAM). Production experience with Infrastructure as Code (Terraform). Solid experience with Docker and container orchestration. Coding Proficiency: You must be comfortable reading and writing production code in Node.js/TypeScript or Python. Experience building or maintaining CI/CD pipelines is a must (GoCD and GitHub Actions preferred). Experience with monitoring tools (Datadog, New Relic, or Prometheus). Experience navigating a polyglot environment (C++ or Rust build processes) is a plus. Knowledge of Database administration (Postgres) using ORMs (Prisma) is a plus. Experience handling infrastructure SOC2 compliance requirements is a plus. Benefits Flexible working hours Stock Options Generous holiday allowance Company pension plan Car parking Enhanced maternity & paternity leave Mental health and wellbeing support Learning and development opportunities About Auterion We are building the leading software platform for AI-powered autonomous systems for enterprise and government customers. Our team is supporting the most important missions and solving the most challenging problems. At Auterion, we bring together the sharpest minds who love to solve the hardest problems. Join a vibrant team built on innovation, openness, and excellence, where you’ll be empowered to develop ideas, collaborate across all levels, and make an impact that matters.",3027,True,,True,False,True,False,False,True,role_forbidden:delivery,"3+ years, autonomous, lead, ownership, take ownership","3+ years, autonomous, lead, ownership, take ownership",False,False,False,False,role_forbidden:delivery
Administrateur système,Job-Room,"La Ferrière, Berner Jura",2026-02-12T07:31:18Z,https://www.adzuna.ch/details/5625792174?utm_medium=api&utm_source=026d8627,https://www.adzuna.ch/details/5625792174,,,"VOTRE MISSION : Rattaché·e à la direction, vous assurez la disponibilité, la sécurité et l’évolution du système d’information de l’entreprise. Dans un environnement industriel exigeant, vous intervenez de manière transversale sur l’infrastructure IT, les outils métiers et la cybersécurité, avec un rôle clé d’interface entre les utilisateurs, les processus opérationnels et les choix technologiques.",administrateur systeme,0,0,63,False,False,strict,adzuna,"VOTRE MISSION : Rattaché·e à la direction, vous assurez la disponibilité, la sécurité et l’évolution du système d’information de l’entreprise. Dans un environnement industriel exigeant, vous intervenez de manière transversale sur l’infrastructure IT, les outils métiers et la cybersécurité, avec un rôle clé d’interface entre les utilisateurs, les processus opérationnels et les choix technologiques. Vous contribuez activement à la structuration et à la fiabilité de l’écosystème informatique, en soutien direct aux activités de production et de gestion. VOTRE PROFIL : - Formation en informatique (niveau ES, HES ou équivalent) - Expérience confirmée d’au minimum 5 ans dans une fonction d’administration système ou d’infrastructure IT, idéalement en environnement PME industrielle - Solides compétences en administration de serveurs, réseaux, sauvegardes et gestion des accès utilisateurs - Bonne maîtrise des enjeux de cybersécurité, de protection des données et de continuité d’activité - Expérience dans la gestion ou l’intégration d’outils métiers (ERP, applications spécialisées, intranet) - Capacité à gérer plusieurs sujets en parallèle, avec méthode, autonomie et sens des priorités - Aisance dans un rôle polyvalent, orienté solutions, avec un bon sens du service interne - À l’aise dans un travail autonome, avec la capacité d’organiser ses priorités et de gérer son périmètre de manière responsable - Doté·e d’un fort sens des responsabilités, faisant preuve de fiabilité et de constance dans la gestion des sujets qui lui sont confiés - Personne de confiance, loyale et discrète, habituée à traiter des informations sensibles et des données confidentielles avec professionnalisme et intégrité",1707,400,"VOTRE MISSION : Rattaché·e à la direction, vous assurez la disponibilité, la sécurité et l’évolution du système d’information de l’entreprise. Dans un environnement industriel exigeant, vous intervenez de manière transversale sur l’infrastructure IT, les outils métiers et la cybersécurité, avec un rôle clé d’interface entre les utilisateurs, les processus opérationnels et les choix technologiques. Vous contribuez activement à la structuration et à la fiabilité de l’écosystème informatique, en soutien direct aux activités de production et de gestion. VOTRE PROFIL : - Formation en informatique (niveau ES, HES ou équivalent) - Expérience confirmée d’au minimum 5 ans dans une fonction d’administration système ou d’infrastructure IT, idéalement en environnement PME industrielle - Solides compétences en administration de serveurs, réseaux, sauvegardes et gestion des accès utilisateurs - Bonne maîtrise des enjeux de cybersécurité, de protection des données et de continuité d’activité - Expérience dans la gestion ou l’intégration d’outils métiers (ERP, applications spécialisées, intranet) - Capacité à gérer plusieurs sujets en parallèle, avec méthode, autonomie et sens des priorités - Aisance dans un rôle polyvalent, orienté solutions, avec un bon sens du service interne - À l’aise dans un travail autonome, avec la capacité d’organiser ses priorités et de gérer son périmètre de manière responsable - Doté·e d’un fort sens des responsabilités, faisant preuve de fiabilité et de constance dans la gestion des sujets qui lui sont confiés - Personne de confiance, loyale et discrète, habituée à traiter des informations sensibles et des données confidentielles avec professionnalisme et intégrité",1707,True,,True,False,False,True,True,False,,"5 ans, experience confirmee","5 ans, experience confirmee",False,False,False,False,exclude_keyword:experience confirmee
QA & Verifications Specialist,Jobgether,Schweiz,2026-02-13T22:15:54Z,https://www.adzuna.ch/details/5628535467?utm_medium=api&utm_source=026d8627,https://www.adzuna.ch/details/5628535467,,,"This position is posted by Jobgether on behalf of a partner company. We are currently looking for a QA & Verifications Specialist in Switzerland. We are seeking a detail-oriented and technically skilled QA & Verifications Specialist to ensure the quality, reliability, and integrity of software products. In this role, you will perform verification and testing across multiple platforms, collaboratin",devops,0,0,62,False,False,strict,adzuna,"This position is posted by Jobgether on behalf of a partner company. We are currently looking for a QA & Verifications Specialist in Switzerland. We are seeking a detail-oriented and technically skilled QA & Verifications Specialist to ensure the quality, reliability, and integrity of software products. In this role, you will perform verification and testing across multiple platforms, collaborating closely with development and DevOps teams. You will contribute to both backend and frontend processes while applying a combination of manual and automated testing methods. The ideal candidate thrives in a fast-paced environment, enjoys problem-solving, and has a proactive approach to identifying and resolving issues. This position offers the opportunity to influence software quality and drive improvements in verification processes. Your work will directly impact the reliability and performance of products delivered to customers.Accountabilities: Conduct verification of software using technical documentation to ensure accuracy and completeness. Build and test software across various programming languages, identifying and resolving build issues. Perform end-to-end testing of application features, using both manual and automated testing methods. Analyze software requirements, dependencies, and documentation to ensure compliance with specifications. Communicate effectively with teams and stakeholders to provide updates and resolve technical issues. Assist in backend, frontend, and DevOps tasks as needed, including CI/CD pipeline maintenance. Contribute to continuous improvement of testing and verification processes to enhance software quality. Requirements: 3+ years of experience in software development or DevOps.2+ years of experience with Linux, Windows, and Mac environments.Basic understanding of backend languages such as Python, Java, NodeJS, and PHP.Familiarity with database and server configurations (MongoDB, SQL, MySQL).Knowledge of Git, front-end languages (HTML, CSS, JavaScript), and AWS technologies is beneficial.Experience with build tools such as msbuild, webpack, and Maven is a plus.Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with the ability to diagnose and resolve complex software issues.Excellent communication, teamwork, and time-management skills, with the ability to handle multiple tasks simultaneously.Adaptability to various programming environments and a willingness to learn new technologies quickly. Benefits: Competitive salary and comprehensive benefits package.Flexible, fully remote working environment.Opportunities for career growth and professional development.Supportive team culture with open communication and feedback.Exposure to diverse technologies and hands-on experience across frontend, backend, and DevOps.Participation in projects that directly impact software quality and customer satisfaction. Why Apply Through Jobgether? We use an AI-powered matching process to ensure your application is reviewed quickly, objectively, and fairly against the role's core requirements. Our system identifies the top-fitting candidates, and this shortlist is then shared directly with the hiring company. The final decision and next steps (interviews, assessments) are managed by their internal team.We appreciate your interest and wish you the best! Why Apply Through Jobgether? Data Privacy Notice: By submitting your application, you acknowledge that Jobgether will process your personal data to evaluate your candidacy and share relevant information with the hiring employer. This processing is based on legitimate interest and pre-contractual measures under applicable data protection laws (including GDPR). You may exercise your rights (access, rectification, erasure, objection) at any time. #LI-CL1We may use artificial intelligence (AI) tools to support parts of the hiring process, such as reviewing applications, analyzing resumes, or assessing responses. These tools assist our recruitment team but do not replace human judgment. Final hiring decisions are ultimately made by humans. If you would like more information about how your data is processed, please contact us.",4142,400,"This position is posted by Jobgether on behalf of a partner company. We are currently looking for a QA & Verifications Specialist in Switzerland. We are seeking a detail-oriented and technically skilled QA & Verifications Specialist to ensure the quality, reliability, and integrity of software products. In this role, you will perform verification and testing across multiple platforms, collaborating closely with development and DevOps teams. You will contribute to both backend and frontend processes while applying a combination of manual and automated testing methods. The ideal candidate thrives in a fast-paced environment, enjoys problem-solving, and has a proactive approach to identifying and resolving issues. This position offers the opportunity to influence software quality and drive improvements in verification processes. Your work will directly impact the reliability and performance of products delivered to customers.Accountabilities: Conduct verification of software using technical documentation to ensure accuracy and completeness. Build and test software across various programming languages, identifying and resolving build issues. Perform end-to-end testing of application features, using both manual and automated testing methods. Analyze software requirements, dependencies, and documentation to ensure compliance with specifications. Communicate effectively with teams and stakeholders to provide updates and resolve technical issues. Assist in backend, frontend, and DevOps tasks as needed, including CI/CD pipeline maintenance. Contribute to continuous improvement of testing and verification processes to enhance software quality. Requirements: 3+ years of experience in software development or DevOps.2+ years of experience with Linux, Windows, and Mac environments.Basic understanding of backend languages such as Python, Java, NodeJS, and PHP.Familiarity with database and server configurations (MongoDB, SQL, MySQL).Knowledge of Git, front-end languages (HTML, CSS, JavaScript), and AWS technologies is beneficial.Experience with build tools such as msbuild, webpack, and Maven is a plus.Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with the ability to diagnose and resolve complex software issues.Excellent communication, teamwork, and time-management skills, with the ability to handle multiple tasks simultaneously.Adaptability to various programming environments and a willingness to learn new technologies quickly. Benefits: Competitive salary and comprehensive benefits package.Flexible, fully remote working environment.Opportunities for career growth and professional development.Supportive team culture with open communication and feedback.Exposure to diverse technologies and hands-on experience across frontend, backend, and DevOps.Participation in projects that directly impact software quality and customer satisfaction. Why Apply Through Jobgether? We use an AI-powered matching process to ensure your application is reviewed quickly, objectively, and fairly against the role's core requirements. Our system identifies the top-fitting candidates, and this shortlist is then shared directly with the hiring company. The final decision and next steps (interviews, assessments) are managed by their internal team.We appreciate your interest and wish you the best! Why Apply Through Jobgether? Data Privacy Notice: By submitting your application, you acknowledge that Jobgether will process your personal data to evaluate your candidacy and share relevant information with the hiring employer. This processing is based on legitimate interest and pre-contractual measures under applicable data protection laws (including GDPR). You may exercise your rights (access, rectification, erasure, objection) at any time. #LI-CL1We may use artificial intelligence (AI) tools to support parts of the hiring process, such as reviewing applications, analyzing resumes, or assessing responses. These tools assist our recruitment team but do not replace human judgment. Final hiring decisions are ultimately made by humans. If you would like more information about how your data is processed, please contact us.",4142,True,,False,False,False,False,False,False,,"3+ years, artificial intelligence","3+ years, artificial intelligence",False,False,False,False,role_forbidden:artificial intelligence
Application Support Engineer,Vitol,"Kanton Genf, Schweiz",2026-02-05T00:53:57Z,https://www.adzuna.ch/details/5614812679?utm_medium=api&utm_source=026d8627,https://www.adzuna.ch/details/5614812679,,,"Job Description We are seeking a proactive and detail-oriented Application Support Engineer to join our dynamic Data Platform & Applications team in Geneva, supporting mission-critical data platform applications in a fast-paced energy trading environment. As part of a global support team, you will provide Level 1 (L1) and Level 2 (L2) support, ensuring high availability, reliability, and performan",application support engineer,0,0,62,False,False,strict,adzuna,"Job Description We are seeking a proactive and detail-oriented Application Support Engineer to join our dynamic Data Platform & Applications team in Geneva, supporting mission-critical data platform applications in a fast-paced energy trading environment. As part of a global support team, you will provide Level 1 (L1) and Level 2 (L2) support, ensuring high availability, reliability, and performance of our data platforms. You will collaborate closely with application development teams, infrastructure teams, and business users across multiple regions to resolve incidents, manage service requests, and drive continuous improvement in support processes. Key Responsibilities: Provide L1 and L2 support for data platform applications, including incident triage, troubleshooting, and resolution. Monitor application health, performance, and data flows using monitoring tools and dashboards. Respond to and resolve user queries, issues, and service requests in a timely manner, maintaining high customer satisfaction. Escalate complex issues to L3 support or development teams, ensuring clear documentation and communication. Perform routine operational tasks such as user access management, data catalog administration, batch job monitoring, and data integrity checks. Collaborate with business users to understand requirements and provide guidance on application functionality and best practices. Maintain and update support documentation, knowledge bases, and runbooks. Identify recurring issues and contribute to root cause analysis and problem management. Support incident and change management processes in line with best practices. Participate in an on-call rotation and provide after-hours support as required.",1719,400,"Job Description We are seeking a proactive and detail-oriented Application Support Engineer to join our dynamic Data Platform & Applications team in Geneva, supporting mission-critical data platform applications in a fast-paced energy trading environment. As part of a global support team, you will provide Level 1 (L1) and Level 2 (L2) support, ensuring high availability, reliability, and performance of our data platforms. You will collaborate closely with application development teams, infrastructure teams, and business users across multiple regions to resolve incidents, manage service requests, and drive continuous improvement in support processes. Key Responsibilities: Provide L1 and L2 support for data platform applications, including incident triage, troubleshooting, and resolution. Monitor application health, performance, and data flows using monitoring tools and dashboards. Respond to and resolve user queries, issues, and service requests in a timely manner, maintaining high customer satisfaction. Escalate complex issues to L3 support or development teams, ensuring clear documentation and communication. Perform routine operational tasks such as user access management, data catalog administration, batch job monitoring, and data integrity checks. Collaborate with business users to understand requirements and provide guidance on application functionality and best practices. Maintain and update support documentation, knowledge bases, and runbooks. Identify recurring issues and contribute to root cause analysis and problem management. Support incident and change management processes in line with best practices. Participate in an on-call rotation and provide after-hours support as required.",1719,True,,True,False,True,False,False,True,role_forbidden: l3 ,,,False,False,False,False,role_forbidden: l3 
DevOps Engineer,21Shares,Schweiz,2026-01-28T21:49:16Z,https://www.adzuna.ch/details/5603985764?utm_medium=api&utm_source=026d8627,https://www.adzuna.ch/details/5603985764,,,"About 21Shares 21Shares makes investing in digital assets as easy as buying shares using your conventional broker or bank. Investors can purchase our crypto ETPs easily, safely and securely in a regulated framework on the SIX Swiss Exchange in USD, Euros and GBP, on BX Swiss in CHF, on Boerse Stuttgart in Euros, on DB Xetra as well as Wiener Boerse ( Vienna Exchange) in Euros. We offer the most ex",platform support engineer,0,0,60,False,False,strict,adzuna,"About 21Shares 21Shares makes investing in digital assets as easy as buying shares using your conventional broker or bank. Investors can purchase our crypto ETPs easily, safely and securely in a regulated framework on the SIX Swiss Exchange in USD, Euros and GBP, on BX Swiss in CHF, on Boerse Stuttgart in Euros, on DB Xetra as well as Wiener Boerse ( Vienna Exchange) in Euros. We offer the most expansive suite of crypto ETPs available on regulated European exchanges. Founded in 2018, 21Shares is led by a team of talented entrepreneurs and experienced professionals from the asset management and banking industry. Headquartered in Zurich, the company has launched several exchange-traded products such as NEAR and ONDO in the last twelve months. Key Responsibilities Infrastructure Management: Provision, maintain, and upgrade AWS and EKS infrastructure using tools like kubectl, Kustomize, and Helm. Automation & IaC: Develop and document reusable Terraform and Terragrunt modules to automate deployments, backups, and routine maintenance. CI/CD & GitOps: Build and refine CI/CD pipelines using GitHub Actions and GitOps workflows, specifically leveraging ArgoCD (including app-of-apps and ApplicationSets). Monitoring & Reliability: Monitor performance and logs via DataDog and AWS CloudWatch, troubleshoot incidents, and take full ownership of the long-term reliability of the systems you build. Data Platform Support: Support data engineers by operating and improving data platforms or data-adjacent infrastructure (e.g., Airflow/MWAA, SQLMesh) in production environments. Streaming Systems: Support and maintain streaming or real-time data systems to ensure consistent data flow and system uptime. Cost Optimization: Analyze cloud spend using AWS Cost Explorer and Infracost to identify waste and implement cost-saving measures. Operational Support: Assist developers with daily operational needs and maintain security/RBAC and resource efficiency within Kubernetes environments. As a DevOps Engineer, you are responsible for maintaining and optimizing our AWS and Kubernetes infrastructure to ensure high reliability, security, and scalability. You will focus on driving cost efficiency, accelerating deployment cycles for developers, and piloting emerging tools that deliver measurable value to the organization. Technical Requirements Kubernetes: Production-level experience with EKS, including Helm and Kustomize. Infrastructure as Code: Proficiency in Terraform and Terragrunt. Cloud & Data Systems: Hands-on experience with the AWS Ecosystem (EC2, ECR, RDS, MSK) and experience operating production data platforms or streaming systems. GitOps: Proven experience with ArgoCD and GitHub Actions automation. Tools: Familiarity with DataDog, MongoDB, and AI-assisted tools like Claude CLI or GitHub Copilot. Attributes: An intrinsic desire to learn and fill in missing skills, with a proactive approach to conducting proof-of-concepts for new DevOps practices.",2972,400,"About 21Shares 21Shares makes investing in digital assets as easy as buying shares using your conventional broker or bank. Investors can purchase our crypto ETPs easily, safely and securely in a regulated framework on the SIX Swiss Exchange in USD, Euros and GBP, on BX Swiss in CHF, on Boerse Stuttgart in Euros, on DB Xetra as well as Wiener Boerse ( Vienna Exchange) in Euros. We offer the most expansive suite of crypto ETPs available on regulated European exchanges. Founded in 2018, 21Shares is led by a team of talented entrepreneurs and experienced professionals from the asset management and banking industry. Headquartered in Zurich, the company has launched several exchange-traded products such as NEAR and ONDO in the last twelve months. Key Responsibilities Infrastructure Management: Provision, maintain, and upgrade AWS and EKS infrastructure using tools like kubectl, Kustomize, and Helm. Automation & IaC: Develop and document reusable Terraform and Terragrunt modules to automate deployments, backups, and routine maintenance. CI/CD & GitOps: Build and refine CI/CD pipelines using GitHub Actions and GitOps workflows, specifically leveraging ArgoCD (including app-of-apps and ApplicationSets). Monitoring & Reliability: Monitor performance and logs via DataDog and AWS CloudWatch, troubleshoot incidents, and take full ownership of the long-term reliability of the systems you build. Data Platform Support: Support data engineers by operating and improving data platforms or data-adjacent infrastructure (e.g., Airflow/MWAA, SQLMesh) in production environments. Streaming Systems: Support and maintain streaming or real-time data systems to ensure consistent data flow and system uptime. Cost Optimization: Analyze cloud spend using AWS Cost Explorer and Infracost to identify waste and implement cost-saving measures. Operational Support: Assist developers with daily operational needs and maintain security/RBAC and resource efficiency within Kubernetes environments. As a DevOps Engineer, you are responsible for maintaining and optimizing our AWS and Kubernetes infrastructure to ensure high reliability, security, and scalability. You will focus on driving cost efficiency, accelerating deployment cycles for developers, and piloting emerging tools that deliver measurable value to the organization. Technical Requirements Kubernetes: Production-level experience with EKS, including Helm and Kustomize. Infrastructure as Code: Proficiency in Terraform and Terragrunt. Cloud & Data Systems: Hands-on experience with the AWS Ecosystem (EC2, ECR, RDS, MSK) and experience operating production data platforms or streaming systems. GitOps: Proven experience with ArgoCD and GitHub Actions automation. Tools: Familiarity with DataDog, MongoDB, and AI-assisted tools like Claude CLI or GitHub Copilot. Attributes: An intrinsic desire to learn and fill in missing skills, with a proactive approach to conducting proof-of-concepts for new DevOps practices.",2972,True,,True,False,True,False,False,True,role_forbidden:data engineer,"cloud & data, data engineer, ownership","cloud & data, data engineer, ownership",False,False,False,False,role_forbidden:data engineer
Technicien IT 100% CDI (H/F/D),Adecco,Schweiz,2026-01-22T06:33:55Z,https://www.adzuna.ch/details/5595151686?utm_medium=api&utm_source=026d8627,https://www.adzuna.ch/details/5595151686,,,"Adecco Vous êtes passionné par les nouvelles technologies et le support informatique ? Rejoignez une entreprise de services informatiques en plein essor car ce poste est fait pour vous : Technicien IT 100% CDI (H/F/D) Responsabilités - Gestion des incidents techniques matériels ou logiciels, assurer la prise en charges des tickets de 2e niveau - Préparation et installation des ordinateurs, configu",support informatique,0,0,60,False,False,strict,adzuna,"Adecco Vous êtes passionné par les nouvelles technologies et le support informatique ? Rejoignez une entreprise de services informatiques en plein essor car ce poste est fait pour vous : Technicien IT 100% CDI (H/F/D) Responsabilités - Gestion des incidents techniques matériels ou logiciels, assurer la prise en charges des tickets de 2e niveau - Préparation et installation des ordinateurs, configuration des postes Windows (PC, périphériques, appareils mobiles), gestion du stock - Selon intérêt, possibilité de prendre part à la formation de l'apprenti et former les utilisateurs - Intervention sur site pour installer le matériel et divers dépannages - Création et mise à jour de la documentation - Veiller à la sécurité des postes de travail Profil - Titulaire d'un CFC d'Informaticien ou diplôme équivalent - Expérience confirmée dans la mise en place de processus informatiques - Maîtrise des environnements Windows et de la suite Microsoft 365 - Compétence confirmée dans l'utilisation des outils de déploiement - Permis de conduire et véhicule personnel indispensables - Résident ou prêt à s'installer en Valais - Excellentes compétences relationnelles et organisationnelles, à l'écoute des besoins, avec un bon esprit d'équipe et une grande autonomie Bénéfices - Un poste fixe au sein d'une entreprise aux projets variés et passionnants - Des pr